<dl id="n53083l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53083l">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53083l"> 83(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> confess, contrit <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53083l"><li>FW 341.25 </li><li><a href="../../flex/md/lexmd.htm#n53083l">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/md/l39md.htm#n53083l">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53083l">MS BL 47480-111</ms> </li><li>JJA 55:200 <a name="mdd6dash" href="../../ff/fdra/mda.htm#mdd6dash">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/md/mdd6.htm#n53083l">Draft: II.3&sect;4.6</a>' </li> </ul><mm class="note">Note: Confession needs must be entire, vocal, humble and sincere, be accompanied with the right attitude, and resolve itself in contrition &mdash; the grief felt by the penitent must arise from a consideration of God&apos;s goodness (presumably outraged by the sin(s) admitted). </mm> </dd></dl>
